column4: heres another question .. i go to install Sun- java .. and it seems that nautilus think im running a AMD 64 processor? and therefore wont let me install it?
i know for a fact that im running an Intel i5??
so you cant install sun SDK on a 64 bi machine? . and why does it say AMD64/
amd64 is just the name given to the architecture
ah, sorry, just noticed you said non-repo
its cool ... this looks like a awesome tool .. so this will build up all the stuff i have installed and chunk it to a CD for easy reinstall?
i only know of its existence, never used it myself but i'm guessing that you change the sources to include cd and then just install like normal
better to stick to default repos
thats shitty advice. dont give it
we can't support other repos here
did i ask for support ? or how to add one
i was merely pointing out that if you add a repo then we can't support it, there have been countless issues here that have resulted from using 3rd party unsupported software
i hope it works for you
